# OctoAcme — Technical Writing & Documentation

## Purpose
Define how documentation is created, maintained, and kept current to support users, stakeholders, and team members.

## Types of Documentation

### 1. Internal Process Documentation
- Project charters and plans
- Design and architecture docs
- Runbooks and playbooks
- Standard operating procedures (SOPs)
- Onboarding guides

### 2. Product Documentation
- User guides and help center articles
- API documentation
- Integration guides
- FAQs and troubleshooting guides
- Feature announcements

### 3. Release Documentation
- Release notes
- Migration guides
- Deployment procedures
- Known issues and workarounds

## Documentation Standards

### Writing Style
- Use clear, concise language (8th-grade reading level target)
- Use active voice and second person ("you")
- Include examples and use cases
- Avoid jargon; define technical terms
- Use consistent terminology across docs

### Structure & Format
- Start with a clear purpose or objective
- Use headings to organize content (H2, H3, H4)
- Include a table of contents for long docs
- Use bulleted/numbered lists for clarity
- Include screenshots or diagrams where helpful
- End with summary and next steps

### Documentation Checklist
- [ ] Purpose and audience clear
- [ ] Content accurate and current
- [ ] Grammar and spelling correct
- [ ] Examples included and tested
- [ ] Links and references valid
- [ ] Consistent formatting and style
- [ ] Accessibility-friendly (alt text for images, proper heading hierarchy)

## Documentation Lifecycle

### Creation
1. Technical Writer gathers information from SMEs (subject matter experts)
2. Outline and structure created
3. Draft written and reviewed by stakeholder
4. Revisions and final review
5. Published and linked from appropriate locations

### Maintenance
- Review and update quarterly or when features change
- Gather feedback from users (support tickets, surveys)
- Mark outdated content clearly
- Archive old versions but keep links functional

### Retirement
- Remove references to deprecated features
- Archive documentation for historical reference
- Redirect users to current documentation

